&lt;br/&gt;
the client accepts and follows these redirects (a trace of the process shows it&amp;#39;s working well) but when &lt;br/&gt;
you ask the getmethod what uri we ended up at using the getURI() method it returns the bastardised &lt;br/&gt;
result:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.adobe.com/Archives/Public/www-xsl-fo/&quot;&gt;http://www.adobe.com/Archives/Public/www-xsl-fo/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
instead of the correct &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-xsl-fo/&quot;&gt;http://lists.w3.org/Archives/Public/www-xsl-fo/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
that the client has actually downloaded.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
using cvsup&amp;#39;d copy showing version string &amp;quot; Jakarta Commons-HttpClient/2.1m1&amp;quot;</description>
